<doc id="617377" wikidata="Q267703" url="?curid=617377" title="Trud">
<text>Trud, translated from Bulgarian, Russian and other Slavic languages as &quot;Labour&quot;, may refer to:

*&quot;Trud&quot; (Bulgarian newspaper)
*&quot;Trud&quot; (Russian newspaper)
*, the republican Voluntary Sports Society of the Russian SFSR

*, a village (&quot;selo&quot;) in Kemerovo Oblast, Russia
*Trud, Plovdiv Province, a village in Plovdiv Province, Bulgaria
*FC Trud Noginsk, former name of FC Znamya Noginsk
*FC Trud Tula, former name of FC Arsenal Tula
*FC Trud Voronezh, former name of FC Fakel Voronezh
*TRNA pseudouridine13 synthase (TruD), an enzyme
* (1921-1999), Soviet World War II fighter pilot, Hero of the Soviet Union 

